A pedestrian was hit and killed by a train on a level crossing near Heidedal in Bloemfontein on Wednesday. Free State police spokesperson Sgt Mahlomola Kareli said they were alerted at 7.30am to the accident near East End Industrial Park. The victim was  believed to have been in his mid-40s and was wearing a black jersey with white stripes. Police  have asked the community to help identify him. A case of culpable homicide has been opened. Kareli appealed to pedestrians to be observant while crossing railway lines: “Cross railroad tracks only at designated pedestrian or road crossings and obey  warning signs and signals. Always stop, look both ways and listen for trains before crossing the tracks.” TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to the Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.